Document: EditorExportPlatformWindows
Path: godot/classes/class_editorexportplatformwindows.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring Windows exports, including application metadata, binary format, code signing, custom templates, debugging, shader baking, SSH remote deployment, and texture formats.

Property Descriptions:
*   application/company_name (String): Company that produced the application. Required.
*   application/console_wrapper_icon (String): Console wrapper icon file. If empty, it falls back to application/icon, then ProjectSettings.application/config/windows_native_icon, and lastly, ProjectSettings.application/config/icon.
*   application/copyright (String): Copyright notice for the bundle visible to the user. Optional.
*   application/d3d12_agility_sdk_multiarch (bool): If true, and application/export_d3d12 is set, the Agility SDK DLLs will be stored in arch-specific subdirectories.
*   application/export_angle (int): If 1, ANGLE libraries are exported with the application. If 0, ANGLE libraries are exported only if ProjectSettings.rendering/gl_compatibility/driver is set to "opengl3_angle".
*   application/export_d3d12 (int): If 1, the Direct3D 12 runtime libraries (Agility SDK, PIX) are exported. If 0, Direct3D 12 libraries are exported only if ProjectSettings.rendering/rendering_device/driver is set to "d3d12".
*   application/file_description (String): File description to be presented to users. Required.
*   application/file_version (String): Version number of the file. Falls back to ProjectSettings.application/config/version if left empty.
*   application/icon (String): Application icon file. If empty, it falls back to ProjectSettings.application/config/windows_native_icon, and then to ProjectSettings.application/config/icon.
*   application/icon_interpolation (int): Interpolation method used to resize application icon.
*   application/modify_resources (bool): If enabled, icon and metadata of the exported executable is set according to the other application/* values.
*   application/product_name (String): Name of the application. Required.
*   application/product_version (String): Application version visible to the user. Falls back to ProjectSettings.application/config/version if left empty.
*   application/trademarks (String): Trademarks and registered trademarks that apply to the file. Optional.
*   binary_format/architecture (String): Application executable architecture. Supported architectures: x86_32, x86_64, and arm64.
*   binary_format/embed_pck (bool): If true, project resources are embedded into the executable.
*   codesign/custom_options (PackedStringArray): Array of additional command line arguments passed to the code signing tool. Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.
*   codesign/description (String): Description of the signed content.
*   codesign/digest_algorithm (int): Digest algorithm to use for creating signature.
*   codesign/enable (bool): If true, executable signing is enabled.
*   codesign/identity (String): PKCS #12 certificate file used to sign executable or certificate SHA-1 hash (if codesign/identity_type is set to "Use certificate store"). Can be overridden with the environment variable GODOT_WINDOWS_CODESIGN_IDENTITY.
*   codesign/identity_type (int): Type of identity to use. Can be overridden with the environment variable GODOT_WINDOWS_CODESIGN_IDENTITY_TYPE.
*   codesign/password (String): Password for the certificate file used to sign executable. Can be overridden with the environment variable GODOT_WINDOWS_CODESIGN_PASSWORD.
*   codesign/timestamp (bool): If true, time-stamp is added to the signature.
*   codesign/timestamp_server_url (String): URL of the time stamp server. If left empty, the default server is used.
*   custom_template/debug (String): Path to the custom export template. If left empty, default template is used.
*   custom_template/release (String): Path to the custom export template. If left empty, default template is used.
*   debug/export_console_wrapper (int): If true, a console wrapper executable is exported alongside the main executable, which allows running the project with enabled console output.
*   shader_baker/enabled (bool): If true, shaders will be compiled and embedded in the application. This option is only supported when using the Forward+ and Mobile renderers. Note: When exporting as a dedicated server, the shader baker is always disabled since no rendering is performed.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/cleanup_script (String): Script code to execute on the remote host when the app is finished. Variables: {temp_dir}, {archive_name}, {exe_name}, {cmd_args}.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/enabled (bool): Enables remote deploy using SSH/SCP.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_scp (String): Array of additional command line arguments passed to the SCP.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/extra_args_ssh (String): Array of additional command line arguments passed to the SSH.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/host (String): Remote host SSH user name and address, in user@address format.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/port (String): Remote host SSH port number.
*   ssh_remote_deploy/run_script (String): Script code to execute on the remote host when running the app. Variables: {temp_dir}, {archive_name}, {exe_name}, {cmd_args}.
*   texture_format/etc2_astc (bool): If true, project textures are exported in the ETC2/ASTC format.
*   texture_format/s3tc_bptc (bool): If true, project textures are exported in the S3TC/BPTC format.